\operatorname{Cov}(X,Y) = \mathrm E\left[ (X-\mathrm E[X])\,(Y-\mathrm E[Y])\right].
 \begin{align} \mathbb C (a+bX,c+dY) &= \mathbb E \left\{[(a+bX) - \mathbb E(a+bX)][(c+dY)-\mathbb E(c+dY)]\right\}\\ &=\mathbb E\left\{[a-a+b(X-\mathbb E(X)][c-c+d(Y-\mathbb E(Y)]\right\}\\ &=bd \>\mathbb E[(X-\mathbb E (X))(Y-\mathbb E(Y))]\\&= bd\>\mathbb C(X,Y) \end{align}  
